The paper also involves information theory, as it discusses the size of formulas, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible sub-category. The use of probabilistic techniques and the study of random processes also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) may be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves combinatorial analysis and the study of boolean functions, which suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible sub-category.
